:"observer-ethical-awards","id":"observer-ethical-awards/observer-ethical-awards-2013-sponsors","fields":{"secureThumbnail":"https://static-secure.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/01/07/Sponsors-140x84.gif","shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/3cqmc","standfirst":"Find out more about the Observer Ethical Awards sponsors","hasStoryPackage":"false","lastModified":"2014-05-21T13:50:55Z","body":"<h2><a href=\"http://www.ecover.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ecover</a></h2><figure data-media-id='gu-image-406372621'><img src='http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/01/07/Ecover-001.jpg' alt='Ecover' width='140' height='84' class='gu-image'/><figcaption></figcaption></figure><p>Ecover has been producing only ecological products from plant and mineral based ingredients for over 30 years. These products harness the power of nature. Ecover's aim is to provide effective sustainable alternatives to be used everyday by people the world over.</p><p>However, Ecover's ecological principles extend far beyond the products they createâ€¦</p><p>Ecover's vision of sustainability takes ecological, economic and social aspects into account from the origins of the raw materials, to the complete biodegradation of the final products. Strict criteria are employed by Ecover's scientists along the way as guidelines for all business operations, from selecting raw materials, through production methods to full decomposition of the end products.</p><p>The products originate from Ecover's unique ecological factories in Belgium and France, both factories are crowned with a green roof that supports wild flowers and sedum and is an effective and efficient temperature-regulator and noise-dampening insulator throughout the year. Thanks to the employees, the factory's energy consumption is kept to a minimum; staff will only turn lighting and heating on when and where it is really necessary and as a result, it is hardly used in the summer months. Ecover also stimulates energy-conscious behaviour outside the factory walls; employees are encouraged to travel to work regularly by bicycle or car share and are remunerated for their efforts.</p><p>Ecover operates with sustainability at its core, constantly innovating and pushing boundaries to create new and more effective products that have minimum impact on the environment, and consistently achieves extraordinary ethical standards with its products, management and production methods. As a pioneer within an increasingly large ecological industry, Ecover is thrilled to be involved with the Observer Ethical Awards 2013.</p><p>We are looking forward to seeing which innovative, inspirational and like-minded people are nominated, and ultimately who will win one of the nine awards on offer. Our hope is that through our day-to-day work and support of the awards we encourage many more people to follow a more sustainable and ethical way of living.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.diy.com/content/marketing/one_planet_home/forest_friendly.jsp?menu=eco\" rel=\"nofollow\"></p><h2>B&amp;Q</h2><p></a></p><figure data-media-id='gu-image-406372618'><img src='http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/01/21/b-q.gif' alt='B&Q' width='140' height='84' class='gu-image'/><figcaption></figcaption></figure><p>As a past winner of the Observer's prestigious Ethical Business award in 2010, B&amp;Q is delighted to continue its support of the Awards by sponsoring the new Products and Services category.</p><p>We're the UK's leading home improvement and garden centre retailer, with a strong heritage in sustainability and are committed to being a responsible retailer.  We've been significantly reducing our own environmental impact and helping our customers to reduce theirs through our One Planet Home programme and our partnership with sustainability charity, Bioregional.  In 2011 we were delighted to be able to announce that the timber in all our 16000 wood or wood containing products is from sources that can be independently verified as sustainable and we launched our Forest Friendly campaign to encourage consumers to question the source of timber in products before they buy â€“ <a href=\"http://www.diy.com/forestfriendly\">www.diy.com/forestfriendly</a>.</p><p>We're also a founding partner to the Ellen MacArthur Foundation and are currently exploring how we might move our business model towards a closed loop one.  We're looking at  how we might re-think and re-design the way we do things to secure a sustainable future for our business and our customers.</p><p>We're delighted to be a part of these prestigious awards and sponsoring the Products and Services category. You can really make someone's year by voting to recognise the great work they've been doing. </p><p><a href=\"http://www.eco-age.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\"></p><h2>Eco Age</h2><p></a></p><figure data-media-id='gu-image-406372619'><img src='http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/01/09/Black-eco-age.gif' alt='Eco Age' width='140' height='84' class='gu-image'/><figcaption></figcaption></figure><p>Eco Age is a luxury sustainable fashion and lifestyle platform and home to the Green Carpet Challenge. Founded by Livia Firth and journalist Lucy Siegle, the GCC is a dynamic project that pairs ethics and aesthetics to profile sustainable style at the world's most high profile red carpet events, with the aim of raising environmental and social justice within the fashion industry.  Eco Age is also comprised of the Eco Consultancy who enable their clients to develop award winning sustainability strategies and demonstrate global sector leadership, environmental responsibility and social progress.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.jupiteronline.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\"></p><h2>Jupiter</h2><p></a></p><figure data-media-id='gu-image-406372622'><img src='http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/01/07/jupiter.jpg' alt='Jupiter logo' width='140' height='84' class='gu-image'/><figcaption></figcaption></figure><p>Jupiter is an award winning fund management firm with one of the best-known brands in the UK investment industry. The company was formed in 1985 and now manages some Â£26.3 billion* on behalf of both private investors and institutions. While investments can fall as well as rise and past performance is not a guide to the future, Jupiter has a strong reputation for delivering outperformance across its range of investment capabilities over the medium to long term. The Company has a long history of green investing and manages several funds of this type. It has an active sustainable investment and governance team.<br /> <br />At challenging economic times such as these it is significant that we are seeing a subtle, but important, shift towards longer-term thinking across a range of financial institutions. There are signs that chairmen are highlighting the importance of ethical leadership in their communications to shareholders via the Annual Report. As with many aspects of behavioural change, corporate responsibility and governance requires more than a token gesture. It will take time for these aspects to become embedded into the corporate DNA, but with the foundations laid during 2012, 2013 could turn out to be a breakthrough year.</p><p><em>*as of 31 December 2012</em>.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.nationalgrid.com/uk\" rel=\"nofollow\"></p><h2>National Grid</h2><p></a></p><figure data-media-id='gu-image-406372623'><img src='http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/01/07/national-grid.jpg' alt='National Grid logo' width='140' height='84' class='gu-image'/><figcaption></figcaption></figure><p>National Grid's job is to connect people to the energy they use. From the warmth and light we rely on at home, and the power which keeps our factories and offices going, to the infrastructure that are essential parts of our modern lifestyle.  In Britain we run systems that deliver gas and electricity across the entire country. In the North Eastern US, we provide power directly to millions of customers. We hold a vital position at the centre of the energy system. We join everything up.</p><p>That puts National Grid at the heart of one of the greatest challenges facing our society; the creation of new sustainable energy solutions and the development of an energy system that can underpin our economic prosperity in the 21st century.</p><p>For this to happen, both our business and our communities need to prosper. This is why we believe in creating shared value by inspiring the next generation of talent, championing great design and preserving resources by respecting and protecting the natural environment and the values at the heart of local communities.</p><h2><a href=\"http://www.virginholidays.co.uk/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Virgin Holidays</a></h2><figure data-media-id='gu-image-406372620'><img src='http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/01/09/virginhols.gif' alt='Virgin Holidays' width='140' height='84' class='gu-image'/><figcaption></figcaption></figure><p>Virgin Holidays was formed in 1985 with a view to selling holiday packages using seats on the new Virgin Atlantic routes to New York, Orlando and Miami.  It has since become one of the largest and most successful scheduled holiday companies in the UK, providing package and tailor-made holidays worldwide.</p><p>Built on the Virgin principles of excellent customer service, high quality and value for money, Virgin Holidays offers maximum convenience and flexibility with an emphasis on fun and excitement. Since its creation, it has gone from strength to strength, establishing itself as the number one holiday company to Florida and the Caribbean and expanding to sell destinations as diverse as Borneo, Buenos Aires, Boston and Bhutan, and holidays ranging from cruises to safaris. The company sells direct to consumers via the web, phone and an expanding network of standalone shops and concessions in department stores across the UK, as well as through long-standing trade partnerships. </p><p>Since 2008, a number of strategic acquisitions have seen Virgin Holidays expand to offer a complete range of holidays. This activity has seen Travel City Direct, Fasttrack Cruises (now Virgin Holidays Cruises) and Fasttrack Ski join the family and in September 2008 a new partnership to create Virgin Holidays+HIP Hotels, targeting travellers seeking a luxury break in one of the world's most distinctive boutique hotels. Finally, in 2009, Bales Worldwide, a specialist in escorted tours, was acquired.  </p><p>Virgin Holidays' success is frequently recognised by both consumer and trade audiences and the high levels of customer satisfaction scores it receives. Indeed, in 2010 the company was voted in to the top ten brands nationally for customer service. Its award wins are manifold, and have included Large Package Holiday Company of the Year (2010) and Best Overall Tour Operator for the USA, Caribbean and Canada in 2012 at the British Travel Awards.  <br />\t\t\t\t                                              <br />The company has a well-founded reputation for industry firsts â€“ whether it was the first CD-Rom brochure, the first underwater wedding or establishing the first customer loyalty scheme for a holiday company. Spring 2008 saw it open the v-room at London Gatwick, the world's only dedicated leisure departure lounge (since enjoyed by a second at Manchester Airport. Other customer-focused innovations rolled out in recent years include a 'Check in/Chill Out' service that enables customers to enjoy their holidays for a few hours more, an in-resort Concierge service that helps customers to plan their holiday before they leave and a series of hotel lounges for customers across the world. </p><p>Virgin Holidays also has a long-standing commitment to sustainable travel. In addition to being one of the founding supporters of the Travel Foundation (a donation from every holiday booking is made, raising an average of Â£250,000 annually), it's Human Nature Collection of holidays features of range of projects from Sri Lanka to Jamaica that have been implemented to 'give something back' to the destinations its customers enjoy visiting, the latest of which â€“ the Branson Centre of Entrepreneurship in the Caribbean â€“ opened in September 2011.</p>","headline":"Observer Ethical Awards 2013: sponsors","trailText":"<p>Find out more about the Observer Ethical Awards sponsors</p>","shouldHideAdverts":"false","publication":"theguardian.com","showInRelatedContent":"true","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2013/01/07/Sponsors-140x84.gif","wordcount":"1509","commentable":"false","internalContentCode":"402006870","allowUgc":"false","isPremoderated":"false","internalPageCode":"1850079","productionOffice":"UK","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2013-01-18T17:09:26Z"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/observer-ethical-awards/observer-ethical-awards-2013-sponsors","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/observer-ethical-awards/observer-ethical-awards-2013-sponsors","tags":[{"id":"observer-ethical-awards/observer-ethical-awards","webTitle":"Observer ethical awards","type":"keyword","sectionId":"observer-ethical-awards","sectionName":"Observer Ethical Awards","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/observer-ethical-awards/observer-ethical-awards","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/observer-ethical-awards/observer-ethical-awards","references":[]},{"id":"tone/event-descriptions","webTitle":"Event descriptions","type":"tone","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/tone/event-descriptions","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/tone/event-descriptions","references":[]},{"id":"type/article","webTitle":"Article","type":"type","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/articles","apiUrl":"http://beta.content.guardianapis.com/type/article","references":[]}],"references":[],"elements":[{"id":"gu-image-406372617","relation":"thumbnail","type":"image","asset